1
00:00:04,546 --> 00:00:09,050
The prosecution presented three grounds
for naming Mr. Serizawa as the culprit.

2
00:00:09,134 --> 00:00:11,344
The first was motive.

3
00:00:11,428 --> 00:00:17,726
They claimed that Serizawa
was stalking the first victim, Yui Sato.

4
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:22,689
Serizawa admits that he contacted Sato
by phone and letters,

5
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:24,357
but he denies the murder.

6
00:00:24,441 --> 00:00:26,693
The second was the murder weapon.

7
00:00:26,776 --> 00:00:31,614
It was judged the marks could match
a belt he possessed.

8
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:33,992
The third was the DNA test.

9
00:00:34,075 --> 00:00:36,161
In order to file a request for a retrial,

10
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:39,039
we need to overturn these grounds.

11
00:00:39,122 --> 00:00:40,040
However,

12
00:00:40,623 --> 00:00:43,793
it might be difficult
with just these documents.

13
00:00:43,877 --> 00:00:47,630
Because your mentor
was in charge of these reports,

14
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:49,966
they must be legit, right?

15
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:52,218
Yes.

16
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:06,524
What happened?

17
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:11,738
It's a breaking news report
of an execution.

18
00:01:18,745 --> 00:01:24,125
<i>Today, one death row inmate</i>
<i>has been executed.</i>

19
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:28,963
<i>It was an extremely brutal crime in which</i>
<i>multiple precious lives were taken</i>

20
00:01:29,047 --> 00:01:31,341
<i>for entirely selfish reasons.</i>

21
00:01:31,925 --> 00:01:32,926
<i>In the end,</i>

22
00:01:33,009 --> 00:01:37,180
<i>after careful deliberation,</i>
<i>it was decided he would be executed.</i>

23
00:01:39,641 --> 00:01:40,892
It's Akiko.

24
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:44,562
Hello, this is Kiryu.

25
00:01:51,027 --> 00:01:51,986
Yes.

26
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:06,751
The one who was executed

27
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:09,504
was not Serizawa.

28
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:14,551
That's good.

29
00:02:20,473 --> 00:02:21,432
It wasn't me today.

30
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:25,562
Don't worry. We will save you.

31
00:02:27,647 --> 00:02:28,773
It wasn't me today.

32
00:02:32,902 --> 00:02:34,070
It wasn't me.

33
00:02:49,419 --> 00:02:52,714
Those documents Professor Kujo had
on the Shiramine case…

34
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:56,426
Could you look for them one more time?

35
00:03:05,059 --> 00:03:07,103
If it's the documents you want,

36
00:03:07,186 --> 00:03:08,479
I found them.

37
00:03:10,982 --> 00:03:11,941
But…

38
00:03:14,027 --> 00:03:15,278
I threw them away.

39
00:03:17,614 --> 00:03:18,907
Could you leave?

40
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:21,367
Don't ever come back again.

41
00:03:24,245 --> 00:03:25,371
<i>Tomorrow,</i>

42
00:03:25,455 --> 00:03:27,373
we're going to Shiramine.

43
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:33,588
What was the town of Shiramine like
at the time?

44
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:41,179
Everyone was exhausted from the anxiety
of when the next murder might happen.

45
00:03:43,973 --> 00:03:46,517
I heard there was even a police officer

46
00:03:46,601 --> 00:03:49,604
who committed suicide due to the stress
of the investigation.

47
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:54,359
In the midst of all that,

48
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:57,779
Shinichi suddenly got arrested.

49
00:03:59,489 --> 00:04:01,366
But Shinichi always said it.

50
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:05,161
He said he definitely didn't do it.

51
00:04:08,539 --> 00:04:12,794
I've believed him this entire time.

52
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:21,719
But recently,

53
00:04:22,762 --> 00:04:24,806
I find myself thinking sometimes

54
00:04:27,308 --> 00:04:28,893
that maybe

55
00:04:29,894 --> 00:04:31,813
we might not make it in time anymore.

56
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:40,655
<i>How long will I have to wait?</i>

57
00:04:40,738 --> 00:04:42,991
Return my daughter, quickly!

58
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:47,245
<i>Yukie is a victim of a serial murder case.</i>

59
00:04:47,328 --> 00:04:49,580
We need to investigate carefully.

60
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:52,250
So what have you found out?

61
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:54,669
You can catch the killer now, right?

62
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:59,173
No traces connecting to the killer
have been found.

63
00:05:00,091 --> 00:05:01,718
They haven't been found?

64
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:05,471
Then what did you perform the autopsy for?

65
00:05:10,226 --> 00:05:11,561
I am terribly sorry.

66
00:05:12,603 --> 00:05:15,606
Anyway,
please let me take my daughter home.

67
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:20,862
The test results
will be ready by tomorrow,

68
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:25,408
so she will be returned to her family.

69
00:05:25,908 --> 00:05:27,160
Please wait

70
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,495
just a little longer.

71
00:05:29,579 --> 00:05:32,123
Yukie Morishita's
judicial autopsy results.

72
00:05:32,206 --> 00:05:34,125
I got what they have as of right now.

73
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:35,793
Thank you very much.

74
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:42,216
This wound…

75
00:05:43,634 --> 00:05:45,511
It's a little strange.

76
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:47,180
Strange?

77
00:05:48,222 --> 00:05:50,099
According to the report,

78
00:05:50,183 --> 00:05:54,896
the injuries to the cheek and lips
could be from when she fell down.

79
00:05:56,522 --> 00:05:58,274
How is that weird?

80
00:05:58,357 --> 00:05:59,817
Depending on the situation,

81
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:02,737
the contents of the report would add up.

82
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:04,405
However,

83
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:10,119
I feel like something's off
with how the wounds were made.

84
00:06:15,917 --> 00:06:19,087
Morishita's body
is still at the university, isn't it?

85
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:23,591
Would it be possible
to let me examine the body?

86
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:28,179
You mean perform an autopsy once more?

87
00:06:28,262 --> 00:06:29,472
Yes.

88
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:35,353
Judging by her father's state,

89
00:06:36,896 --> 00:06:38,481
I think it will be difficult.

90
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:44,779
The documents Professor Kujo had
have already been disposed of.

91
00:06:46,447 --> 00:06:48,449
<i>Ms. Morishita's body</i>

92
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:52,745
might be the only clue
to clear Mr. Serizawa's false accusation.

93
00:07:17,353 --> 00:07:20,731
<i>It has been 15 years</i>
<i>since Yui passed away.</i>

94
00:07:21,482 --> 00:07:22,733
The other day,

95
00:07:22,817 --> 00:07:27,071
I saw on the news
that the killer's family is…

96
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:30,575
claiming his innocence.

97
00:07:33,369 --> 00:07:34,579
Your daughter

98
00:07:35,371 --> 00:07:38,749
was being stalked by Serizawa, right?

99
00:07:39,792 --> 00:07:40,877
That's right.

100
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:44,297
She refused him,
because she had a boyfriend.

101
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:47,425
Even so, he wouldn't give up.

102
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:50,928
I told her

103
00:07:51,637 --> 00:07:53,931
we should go to the police.

104
00:07:56,517 --> 00:07:57,810
But Yui said

105
00:07:59,187 --> 00:08:01,772
there was no need to worry that much.

106
00:08:05,234 --> 00:08:06,235
Um,

107
00:08:07,403 --> 00:08:09,655
her boyfriend at the time…

108
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:12,742
Does he still live nearby?

109
00:08:14,827 --> 00:08:17,246
He passed away.

110
00:08:18,706 --> 00:08:19,707
What?

111
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:22,293
He followed Yui.

112
00:08:23,711 --> 00:08:25,755
He committed suicide.

113
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:30,384
I should have…

114
00:08:33,554 --> 00:08:36,641
gone to the police,
even if she didn't want to.

115
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:46,692
I will absolutely never forgive Serizawa

116
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:49,737
for taking Yui away from me.

117
00:08:58,704 --> 00:09:01,415
So I told my boss.

118
00:09:02,124 --> 00:09:03,501
"It doesn't add up!"

119
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:05,127
Wow, awesome.

120
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:06,212
Right?

121
00:09:06,295 --> 00:09:08,506
I just can't ignore those things,
you know?

122
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:09,882
Strange things are--

123
00:09:09,966 --> 00:09:12,009
Hey, it's about that time, isn't it?

124
00:09:12,093 --> 00:09:14,053
Shall we head home then?

125
00:09:15,429 --> 00:09:17,640
What are you saying?
On to the next spot!

126
00:09:17,723 --> 00:09:18,808
What?

127
00:09:18,891 --> 00:09:21,477
-Excuse me! Bill please.
-Okay.

128
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:23,854
We need Dr. Honda now more than ever.

129
00:09:23,938 --> 00:09:26,065
The burden is too heavy for just us!

130
00:09:26,148 --> 00:09:27,024
We can't!

131
00:09:27,108 --> 00:09:31,320
He left yesterday to help with autopsies
at Kyomei University, so he's busy.

132
00:09:40,288 --> 00:09:41,205
Mr. Morishita.

133
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:46,085
Do you have a moment?

134
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:48,087
What is it?

135
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:51,591
I had a forensic scientist

136
00:09:51,674 --> 00:09:55,553
from an organization called MEJ
look at Yukie's autopsy results.

137
00:09:55,636 --> 00:09:56,887
That doctor said

138
00:09:56,971 --> 00:10:00,474
there is something strange
with the wounds on Yukie's face.

139
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:07,106
Could you let us

140
00:10:08,357 --> 00:10:12,111
examine Yukie's body just one more time?

141
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:17,575
You mean
you want to perform another autopsy?

142
00:10:21,203 --> 00:10:22,038
Yes.

143
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:27,918
Don't mess with me!

144
00:10:28,919 --> 00:10:30,755
Yukie was murdered,

145
00:10:30,838 --> 00:10:32,423
and even autopsied.

146
00:10:33,424 --> 00:10:36,636
Are you telling me
to hurt that child again?

147
00:10:37,845 --> 00:10:41,223
I understand your feelings very well.

148
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:45,144
But that doctor

149
00:10:45,978 --> 00:10:49,899
has found so many small contradictions
left on bodies

150
00:10:49,982 --> 00:10:53,486
that nobody else had noticed.

151
00:10:54,987 --> 00:10:57,573
He has always uncovered the truth.

152
00:10:58,741 --> 00:10:59,950
He will…

153
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:06,415
find the contradiction
left behind by Yukie for us.

154
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:19,512
Please…

155
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:22,515
I beg you.

156
00:11:24,475 --> 00:11:29,271
I don't want there to be any other
victims like Yukie ever again.

157
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:40,533
I am not going to change
the time for her wake.

158
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:47,456
Make sure to return her

159
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:50,084
by 6:00 p.m. tonight.

160
00:12:00,469 --> 00:12:01,887
Thank you very much.

161
00:12:05,724 --> 00:12:07,685
By 6:00 p.m.?

162
00:12:07,768 --> 00:12:10,771
Taking into account
the time to deliver the body back,

163
00:12:10,855 --> 00:12:13,107
we only have about two hours left.

164
00:12:14,650 --> 00:12:15,693
Will we make it?

165
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:19,864
We just have to do what we can.

166
00:12:19,947 --> 00:12:20,948
Let's hurry.

167
00:12:21,031 --> 00:12:22,032
Yes.

168
00:12:22,616 --> 00:12:23,742
I will help too.

169
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:51,520
What are you all doing here?

170
00:12:52,646 --> 00:12:55,608
I was at Kyomei University today
to help them out.

171
00:12:56,734 --> 00:13:01,155
I happened to hear Ms. Dojima
talking to the bereaved father.

172
00:13:05,993 --> 00:13:07,578
I don't know all the details,

173
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:10,998
but you have little time
for the autopsy, right?

174
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:15,544
So, I thought it would be better
to have as many people as possible,

175
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:17,630
so I hurried and got everyone together.

176
00:13:18,422 --> 00:13:22,593
I also managed to leave early somehow.

177
00:13:25,179 --> 00:13:29,934
I don't know the details of why you
are staying at MEJ, Dr. Masumi.

178
00:13:31,810 --> 00:13:32,645
But,

179
00:13:33,312 --> 00:13:36,565
I understand that this autopsy
is not just an ordinary autopsy.

180
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:39,652
Please let us help too.

181
00:13:40,152 --> 00:13:42,363
We want to help you, Dr. Masumi.

182
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:49,954
Thank you very much.

183
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:55,292
Well, we don't have much time.

184
00:13:55,876 --> 00:13:57,002
Shall we get to it?

185
00:13:57,086 --> 00:13:58,087
-Yes.
-Yes.

186
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:13,602
After checking the wounds
on the left cheek and lips,

187
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:16,355
we found out what Dr. Masumi
thought was strange.

188
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:19,108
The positions of the wounds are off.

189
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:20,776
Off?

190
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:23,779
In the report,
the wounds on the left cheek and lips

191
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:26,282
are described as beind caused
from falling down.

192
00:14:26,365 --> 00:14:30,160
The wounds on Yukie's body
were concentrated on the left side.

193
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:33,581
It is natural to think
she fell on her left side.

194
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:34,498
But,

195
00:14:34,582 --> 00:14:37,084
only the wound on the lip
is closer to the front.

196
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:39,086
If she fell to the ground
with her left side down,

197
00:14:39,169 --> 00:14:40,880
it would be difficult
to get a wound there.

198
00:14:41,463 --> 00:14:42,673
So,

199
00:14:42,756 --> 00:14:45,217
we tried re-examining
the inside of the mouth once more.

200
00:14:45,301 --> 00:14:47,261
There was bleeding inside the oral cavity,

201
00:14:47,344 --> 00:14:49,263
and not only was there a wound on the lip,

202
00:14:49,346 --> 00:14:51,932
but the upper left canine tooth
was slightly chipped.

203
00:14:52,016 --> 00:14:54,226
Judging from the condition
of the cross-section,

204
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:56,645
the tooth was chipped very recently.

205
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:58,564
In other words,

206
00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:02,693
it means there is a possibility
that Yukie bit the culprit.

207
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:05,487
What?

208
00:15:07,114 --> 00:15:08,324
In that case,

209
00:15:08,407 --> 00:15:10,993
the blood adhering inside the oral cavity

210
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:15,581
would be a mixture of Yukie's
and the culprit's.

211
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:18,709
If we do a DNA test on this blood,

212
00:15:19,585 --> 00:15:22,796
we might be able to identify the culprit.

213
00:15:27,426 --> 00:15:29,511
As a result of the DNA test,

214
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:32,598
a man named Koji Uchiyama has surfaced.

215
00:15:33,474 --> 00:15:37,478
Uchiyama was arrested in 2015
on charges of injury, served time,

216
00:15:37,561 --> 00:15:39,355
and was released at the end of last year.

217
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:41,690
The timing of Uchiyama's release

218
00:15:41,774 --> 00:15:44,526
overlaps with
when the serial killings began.

219
00:15:44,610 --> 00:15:47,780
Furthermore, it seems Uchiyama
used to be an informant

220
00:15:47,863 --> 00:15:50,199
who leaked underworld information
to the police.

221
00:15:51,408 --> 00:15:55,037
It wouldn't be surprising if he knew
the police's investigative methods.

222
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:59,625
That's why absolutely no evidence
came up in the investigation until now.

223
00:16:32,449 --> 00:16:33,742
Stop right there!

224
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:42,960
You smell nice, ma'am.

225
00:16:45,879 --> 00:16:47,339
Secured him!

226
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:51,677
We couldn't find any direct evidence
at Uchiyama's home.

227
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:56,765
At this rate, it may be difficult
to tie Uchiyama to the other five murders.

228
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:08,902
You killed Ms. Morishita, didn't you?

229
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:15,284
We found your DNA on her body,
you can't talk your way out of this.

230
00:17:15,367 --> 00:17:17,828
I have no intention of doing so.

231
00:17:19,496 --> 00:17:20,706
As you say,

232
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:23,792
<i>I am the one who killed Morishita.</i>

233
00:17:27,588 --> 00:17:29,339
It wasn't just her, right?

234
00:17:30,299 --> 00:17:33,093
-The other five were also--
-That was me as well.

235
00:17:37,097 --> 00:17:42,019
Tamura, Shimizu,
Ikezawa, Konishi, Nomoto, all of them.

236
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:43,812
I killed all of them.

237
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:48,567
I thought I would let all who mocked me

238
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:52,154
know just what type of person I really am.

239
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:04,458
What about Shiramine 15 years ago?

240
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:12,883
That was you too, wasn't it?

241
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:17,262
No, it wasn't.

242
00:18:20,641 --> 00:18:22,267
That wasn't me.

243
00:18:32,486 --> 00:18:36,782
Uchiyama confessed to
all of the current murders.

244
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:37,699
But,

245
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:41,787
he flat out denies the Shiramine murders.

246
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:43,247
In that case,

247
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:46,208
Uchiyama wasn't the culprit
in Shiramine after all?

248
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:47,126
No.

249
00:18:49,086 --> 00:18:51,463
He was definitely involved in it.

250
00:18:56,844 --> 00:18:57,928
In the first place,

251
00:18:58,011 --> 00:19:01,473
why would he admit to all five murders
when we had no evidence on him?

252
00:19:03,016 --> 00:19:04,768
After being released from prison,

253
00:19:04,852 --> 00:19:07,563
he had almost no money
and lived in terrible poverty.

254
00:19:08,063 --> 00:19:09,189
Probably,

255
00:19:10,023 --> 00:19:13,861
he wanted to get back at society
for looking down on him.

256
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:16,697
So he confessed

257
00:19:17,739 --> 00:19:22,119
to show everyone that he was the one
who committed those murders.

258
00:19:22,202 --> 00:19:24,496
If that's his motive,

259
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:28,041
why would he deny the Shiramine incident?

260
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:32,004
<i>According to a friend at the police,</i>

261
00:19:32,087 --> 00:19:35,549
Uchiyama apparently does not admit
that he's involved in the Shiramine case.

262
00:19:35,632 --> 00:19:37,593
If he admits to the crime,

263
00:19:37,676 --> 00:19:39,428
things will get quite bad.

264
00:19:40,596 --> 00:19:43,640
Serizawa's family
will surely request a retrial.

265
00:19:44,141 --> 00:19:46,727
If a decision to commence
a retrial is issued,

266
00:19:47,227 --> 00:19:49,730
we will have to file an immediate appeal.

267
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:52,482
What is an appeal?

268
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:55,360
It means the prosecution
objects to the court's decision

269
00:19:55,444 --> 00:19:57,279
to start a retrial.

270
00:19:57,779 --> 00:20:01,241
If that happens, the retrial
will be contested all over again,

271
00:20:01,325 --> 00:20:04,077
and it will take several years
to reach a conclusion.

272
00:20:04,161 --> 00:20:05,746
That's terrible.

273
00:20:05,829 --> 00:20:07,080
That's so cruel.

274
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:12,211
Mr. Serizawa has already had
15 years of his life stolen from him.

275
00:20:13,462 --> 00:20:15,839
<i>If the Shiramine charge is overturned,</i>

276
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:20,052
both you and I will lose
our futures as prosecutors.

277
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:22,471
It will be over.

278
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:27,601
Our decision was one of justice.

279
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:33,398
Our decision was one of justice…

280
00:20:44,618 --> 00:20:45,702
What's wrong?

281
00:20:45,786 --> 00:20:49,248
Mr. Yamazaki asked me to compile
these mental care reports

282
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:51,416
we got from local municipalities.

283
00:20:52,209 --> 00:20:53,627
Mental care?

284
00:20:53,710 --> 00:20:56,797
Municipalities in areas where
major incidents or disasters occurred

285
00:20:56,880 --> 00:21:01,093
report to the government regarding their
response to residents' mental concerns.

286
00:21:02,970 --> 00:21:04,763
I heard there was even a police officer

287
00:21:04,846 --> 00:21:08,058
who committed suicide due to the stress
of the prolonged investigation.

288
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:11,019
When did they start doing that?

289
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:13,855
Over twenty years ago.

290
00:21:14,439 --> 00:21:16,692
The older ones haven't been digitized.

291
00:21:23,156 --> 00:21:26,368
PSYCHOLOGICAL EFFECTS
OF MAJOR EVENTS IN SHIRAMINE

292
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:48,557
<i>Yes?</i>

293
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:49,933
Sorry to disturb you.

294
00:21:50,017 --> 00:21:53,437
I am Kiryu from Medical Examiner Japan.

295
00:21:54,354 --> 00:21:58,275
Could I ask you some questions regarding
the Shiramine incident

296
00:21:58,358 --> 00:21:59,568
from 15 years ago?

297
00:22:00,319 --> 00:22:02,571
MAHO KIRYU

298
00:22:04,281 --> 00:22:05,198
Yes?

299
00:22:05,782 --> 00:22:08,118
There's something
that caught my attention.

300
00:22:08,201 --> 00:22:10,537
I'm in Shiramine.

301
00:22:11,121 --> 00:22:14,499
I want to tell you something, Doctor.

302
00:22:17,753 --> 00:22:20,422
Based on the evidence everyone gathered,

303
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:22,966
we have filed a request for a retrial.

304
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:24,634
But,

305
00:22:25,260 --> 00:22:28,013
the prosecution will undoubtedly

306
00:22:29,765 --> 00:22:31,767
try to buy time by filing an appeal.

307
00:22:35,812 --> 00:22:39,816
There is only one thing left
that we can do.

308
00:22:44,488 --> 00:22:46,698
A petition to the prosecution.

309
00:22:48,992 --> 00:22:52,245
We will go demand
that they do not file an appeal

310
00:22:52,329 --> 00:22:55,290
if the commencement
of the retrial is granted.

311
00:23:01,338 --> 00:23:02,255
Please.

312
00:23:03,715 --> 00:23:07,344
Will you all help me with this?

313
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:19,731
PUBLIC PROSECUTION

314
00:23:36,873 --> 00:23:39,668
I have come here today with my lawyer

315
00:23:39,751 --> 00:23:44,965
to respectfully ask the prosecution
to refrain from filing an appeal.

316
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:47,384
We are justice.

317
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:52,055
We believed that the perpetrator
of the current serial murder case

318
00:23:52,139 --> 00:23:56,101
and the true culprit of the Shiramine
case were the same person.

319
00:23:56,184 --> 00:23:59,771
Amidst this, Koji Uchiyama was arrested.

320
00:24:00,522 --> 00:24:03,775
Koji Uchiyama denies involvement
in the Shiramine case.

321
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:06,444
Without evidence,
that is just speculation.

322
00:24:06,528 --> 00:24:07,487
Indeed.

323
00:24:07,571 --> 00:24:11,449
Mr. Uchiyama denied involvement
in the Shiramine incident.

324
00:24:12,492 --> 00:24:16,371
Do you have any proof that I was
the culprit of that old case?

325
00:24:16,454 --> 00:24:17,956
If you do, please show me.

326
00:24:25,630 --> 00:24:27,132
You're right.

327
00:24:28,592 --> 00:24:31,678
There is no evidence whatsoever.

328
00:24:34,556 --> 00:24:37,934
Regarding the current
serial murder case, even…

329
00:24:38,643 --> 00:24:41,730
<i>in terms of evidence that you killed</i>
<i>the other five girls</i>

330
00:24:41,813 --> 00:24:43,857
besides Yukie Morishita.

331
00:24:45,108 --> 00:24:46,109
There is none.

332
00:24:46,693 --> 00:24:47,652
What?

333
00:24:48,486 --> 00:24:50,197
The only case with evidence

334
00:24:50,989 --> 00:24:54,910
is the murder of Yukie Morishita.

335
00:24:54,993 --> 00:24:59,998
You are not a serial killer.
You aren't anything at all.

336
00:25:01,416 --> 00:25:03,335
You boast about it,

337
00:25:03,418 --> 00:25:05,712
but you're nothing but a petty criminal.

338
00:25:07,714 --> 00:25:09,758
No, no, no, no!

339
00:25:10,884 --> 00:25:13,261
I killed the other five too.

340
00:25:13,345 --> 00:25:14,554
Really?

341
00:25:15,597 --> 00:25:18,308
Are you really that impressive a man?

342
00:25:19,184 --> 00:25:20,894
Too bad, though.

343
00:25:20,977 --> 00:25:23,271
There's no evidence.

344
00:25:29,653 --> 00:25:31,696
If there is any, please show me.

345
00:25:37,577 --> 00:25:39,079
I…

346
00:25:40,705 --> 00:25:43,416
killed six people
without getting caught by the police.

347
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:44,751
I did it!

348
00:25:47,003 --> 00:25:49,506
I killed all three people

349
00:25:49,589 --> 00:25:51,883
from the Shiramine case, too!

350
00:25:55,387 --> 00:25:57,430
Uchiyama suddenly admitted

351
00:25:57,514 --> 00:26:00,308
to his involvement
in the Shiramine murders.

352
00:26:01,643 --> 00:26:02,644
However, this…

353
00:26:03,853 --> 00:26:05,063
was a lie.

354
00:26:06,189 --> 00:26:07,399
A lie?

355
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:10,527
All three of them?

356
00:26:10,610 --> 00:26:11,945
That's right.

357
00:26:14,114 --> 00:26:17,325
That's a lie just to get
public attention, isn't it?

358
00:26:17,409 --> 00:26:18,368
No!

359
00:26:18,451 --> 00:26:19,494
Come on!

360
00:26:21,079 --> 00:26:26,126
The ones you killed were only the second
and third victim, right?

361
00:26:29,462 --> 00:26:31,047
The second and third?

362
00:26:31,548 --> 00:26:33,216
What are you talking about?

363
00:26:34,092 --> 00:26:38,972
We have done our investigation
under the assumption that the perpetrator

364
00:26:39,055 --> 00:26:43,560
of the current serial murder case
was the same as the Shiramine case.

365
00:26:46,271 --> 00:26:47,439
However,

366
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:50,275
in the Shiramine incident,

367
00:26:50,775 --> 00:26:52,777
there were two perpetrators.

368
00:26:53,903 --> 00:26:55,030
Two?

369
00:26:56,489 --> 00:26:58,199
According to her family,

370
00:26:58,283 --> 00:27:00,910
<i>Yui Sato was being stalked.</i>

371
00:27:01,911 --> 00:27:07,375
We thought that the stalker might be
the culprit who murdered Sato.

372
00:27:07,459 --> 00:27:10,003
That's why it's Serizawa.

373
00:27:10,086 --> 00:27:13,631
Serizawa approached the victim
but was rejected,

374
00:27:13,715 --> 00:27:16,426
leading him to murder her
out of resentment.

375
00:27:16,509 --> 00:27:20,138
That is the story
fabricated by the prosecution.

376
00:27:20,221 --> 00:27:23,767
In reality, there was another stalker.

377
00:27:25,310 --> 00:27:27,771
Ms. Sato was troubled by the stalker,

378
00:27:27,854 --> 00:27:30,607
so her mother suggested
to consult the police.

379
00:27:31,858 --> 00:27:32,817
But,

380
00:27:33,651 --> 00:27:35,320
she didn't do so.

381
00:27:37,614 --> 00:27:41,117
Why didn't Yui Sato consult the police?

382
00:27:41,910 --> 00:27:44,746
It wasn't to avoid causing trouble
within her family,

383
00:27:45,455 --> 00:27:48,208
nor because she disliked
making a big deal.

384
00:27:49,376 --> 00:27:51,086
It was because that stalker

385
00:27:52,003 --> 00:27:54,089
was a police officer.

386
00:27:55,548 --> 00:27:57,425
What grounds do you have for saying that?

387
00:27:57,509 --> 00:27:59,552
No such testimony has come from anywhere.

388
00:27:59,636 --> 00:28:02,472
In fact, Serizawa has admitted
to the stalking behavior.

389
00:28:02,555 --> 00:28:05,350
In Shiramine at the time,
there was a rumor

390
00:28:05,433 --> 00:28:09,354
that two people had committed suicide
in connection with the murder.

391
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:13,358
One was Yui Sato's boyfriend, Sho Mizuta.

392
00:28:13,441 --> 00:28:16,820
It was said that he committed suicide
due to the shock of losing her.

393
00:28:16,903 --> 00:28:18,988
The other was a police officer,

394
00:28:19,072 --> 00:28:22,826
who supposedly chose death due to
the stress of the prolonged investigation.

395
00:28:22,909 --> 00:28:24,369
<i>Following the incident,</i>

396
00:28:24,452 --> 00:28:28,081
<i>Shiramine compiled a report</i>
<i>on the consultation status and responses,</i>

397
00:28:28,164 --> 00:28:30,542
<i>and submitted it to the MHLW.</i>

398
00:28:30,625 --> 00:28:32,544
<i>In that report,</i>

399
00:28:32,627 --> 00:28:36,548
<i>it was written that Sho Mizuta, who worked</i>
<i>at the Shiramine Police Station,</i>

400
00:28:36,631 --> 00:28:40,176
<i>was found hanging at his home.</i>

401
00:28:41,469 --> 00:28:42,846
In other words,

402
00:28:43,638 --> 00:28:49,978
Yui Sato's boyfriend and Sho Mizuta,
the police officer who committed suicide,

403
00:28:51,271 --> 00:28:53,231
were in fact the same person.

404
00:28:57,694 --> 00:28:59,779
So what if they are the same person?

405
00:29:00,363 --> 00:29:03,658
That doesn't constitute proof
that he murdered Yui Sato.

406
00:29:04,325 --> 00:29:05,869
We do have proof.

407
00:29:11,791 --> 00:29:12,917
Mr. and Mrs. Mizuta.

408
00:29:14,252 --> 00:29:15,795
I understand

409
00:29:15,879 --> 00:29:18,923
that you have been suffering
for a long time over your son.

410
00:29:19,007 --> 00:29:20,091
But,

411
00:29:21,217 --> 00:29:25,013
both Shinichi Serizawa
and his older sister

412
00:29:25,096 --> 00:29:27,390
have also been suffering for 15 years.

413
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:31,936
Please…

414
00:29:33,605 --> 00:29:36,274
Would you tell me the truth?

415
00:29:43,782 --> 00:29:44,908
We are

416
00:29:45,575 --> 00:29:48,411
so sorry.

417
00:29:50,955 --> 00:29:52,916
Sho Mizuta's parents

418
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:56,377
have admitted to their son's crime.

419
00:30:06,596 --> 00:30:09,974
Two months before the incident,
Yui Sato told Mizuta

420
00:30:10,809 --> 00:30:13,645
that she wanted to break up.

421
00:30:13,728 --> 00:30:17,524
Unable to accept it,
he kept pressing her to get back together.

422
00:30:18,817 --> 00:30:21,236
However, in the end,

423
00:30:21,945 --> 00:30:24,697
that gradually turned
into him stalking her.

424
00:30:25,406 --> 00:30:27,116
On the night of the incident,

425
00:30:28,451 --> 00:30:32,539
Mizuta waited for Sato
as she finished her part-time job

426
00:30:32,622 --> 00:30:34,207
and murdered her.

427
00:30:34,290 --> 00:30:37,919
He told his parents this while crying.

428
00:30:39,337 --> 00:30:40,296
Then,

429
00:30:40,755 --> 00:30:43,049
when his parents left him alone for a bit,

430
00:30:44,259 --> 00:30:46,636
he had taken his own life.

431
00:30:49,389 --> 00:30:51,641
The one who murdered Yui Sato

432
00:30:52,141 --> 00:30:53,810
was Sho Mizuta.

433
00:30:55,019 --> 00:30:57,647
This fact has been hidden

434
00:30:58,481 --> 00:31:00,942
by his parents for 15 years.

435
00:31:01,943 --> 00:31:03,528
That is just…

436
00:31:05,238 --> 00:31:08,199
the parents' delusion.

437
00:31:08,283 --> 00:31:11,119
There is no objective evidence
that he did it--

438
00:31:13,496 --> 00:31:17,709
This is his belt that we borrowed
from Mizuta's parents' home.

439
00:31:18,543 --> 00:31:24,424
This belt perfectly matches the
strangulation marks on Yui Sato's neck.

440
00:31:25,091 --> 00:31:28,052
However, Professor Kujo's expert opinion

441
00:31:28,136 --> 00:31:32,557
concluded that the murder weapon
was consistent with Serizawa's belt.

442
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:34,434
Are you saying he was mistaken?

443
00:31:34,517 --> 00:31:38,897
"Consistent" and "matching" sound similar,
but they are different.

444
00:31:39,772 --> 00:31:42,650
In the sense that she was strangled
with a leather strap,

445
00:31:42,734 --> 00:31:44,360
it is indeed consistent.

446
00:31:45,570 --> 00:31:47,071
But Mizuta's belt

447
00:31:47,780 --> 00:31:52,368
is a perfect match with
the width of the strangulation marks.

448
00:31:57,081 --> 00:32:01,920
In other words, the murders committed
by Sho Mizuta and Koji Uchiyama

449
00:32:02,003 --> 00:32:05,548
were entirely separate crimes, and yet

450
00:32:05,632 --> 00:32:08,843
they were treated
as a single serial murder case.

451
00:32:08,927 --> 00:32:11,763
That was the reality
of the Shiramine case.

452
00:32:14,098 --> 00:32:17,518
Even though there were two killers,
the police at the time

453
00:32:17,602 --> 00:32:20,647
assumed that there was only one culprit.

454
00:32:20,730 --> 00:32:22,023
That's why

455
00:32:22,523 --> 00:32:24,943
the investigation was
full of contradictions

456
00:32:25,443 --> 00:32:28,446
and nobody could grasp
the full scope of the case.

457
00:32:29,864 --> 00:32:31,282
And this was exactly

458
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:35,036
what Koji Uchiyama was aiming for.

459
00:32:35,620 --> 00:32:38,081
As an informant,

460
00:32:39,248 --> 00:32:42,418
you knew that the police
were unable to name a suspect

461
00:32:42,502 --> 00:32:47,465
in the murder of Yui Sato,
and that the scene was in chaos.

462
00:32:48,049 --> 00:32:49,759
In the midst of that,

463
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:56,307
having a financial dispute
with the second female victim,

464
00:32:57,350 --> 00:33:04,023
you copied the first murder
to make your own murder blend into it.

465
00:33:05,817 --> 00:33:06,859
And,

466
00:33:08,194 --> 00:33:11,906
so that your existence wouldn't be traced
through the victim's acquaintances,

467
00:33:11,990 --> 00:33:14,617
you chose a woman
with absolutely no connection to you

468
00:33:14,701 --> 00:33:16,661
and killed her as the third victim.

469
00:33:17,954 --> 00:33:22,208
The reason you didn't admit
to the Shiramine incident was because…

470
00:33:26,921 --> 00:33:28,506
you were afraid

471
00:33:29,507 --> 00:33:33,761
it would be revealed that you were just

472
00:33:35,179 --> 00:33:39,308
a small-time criminal
who jumped on someone else's murder.

473
00:33:41,185 --> 00:33:43,521
Just as Uchiyama planned,

474
00:33:44,522 --> 00:33:46,691
the police reached a dead end.

475
00:33:46,774 --> 00:33:48,401
As a result of their impatience,

476
00:33:48,484 --> 00:33:52,488
they framed Mr. Serizawa as the culprit
to settle the case.

477
00:33:53,072 --> 00:33:55,616
To turn Mr. Serizawa into the culprit,

478
00:33:55,700 --> 00:33:59,871
they chose to ignore
the inconvenient contradictions.

479
00:34:00,580 --> 00:34:01,831
And that…

480
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:06,252
applies to the past version of me as well.

481
00:34:08,713 --> 00:34:13,926
Despite noticing a contradiction
in Professor Kujo's medical report,

482
00:34:15,094 --> 00:34:16,846
I gave up on blowing the whistle

483
00:34:17,388 --> 00:34:18,806
and ran away.

484
00:34:21,601 --> 00:34:22,894
Because of that,

485
00:34:23,478 --> 00:34:26,481
15 years were taken away from Mr. Serizawa

486
00:34:27,690 --> 00:34:30,276
and from his family.

487
00:34:36,783 --> 00:34:41,079
We cannot give back the time they've lost.

488
00:34:42,246 --> 00:34:46,417
That's why we must at least
not take away the opportunity

489
00:34:47,335 --> 00:34:49,337
for Mr. Serizawa and his family

490
00:34:49,921 --> 00:34:51,964
to reclaim their honor.

491
00:35:07,730 --> 00:35:08,856
Please,

492
00:35:09,732 --> 00:35:11,484
make a wise decision.

493
00:35:12,026 --> 00:35:13,111
Please.

494
00:35:24,664 --> 00:35:26,457
I understand what you are saying.

495
00:35:26,541 --> 00:35:27,625
However,

496
00:35:27,708 --> 00:35:33,131
an appeal is a legitimate procedure
granted to the prosecution.

497
00:35:34,715 --> 00:35:37,176
In order to seek a careful examination,

498
00:35:37,927 --> 00:35:40,221
the policy to file an appeal--

499
00:35:58,948 --> 00:36:00,867
Ota! What are you doing?

500
00:36:01,576 --> 00:36:02,451
Stop it!

501
00:36:07,331 --> 00:36:10,334
The responsibility
for taking 15 years from Mr. Serizawa

502
00:36:11,460 --> 00:36:12,837
lies with us.

503
00:36:17,133 --> 00:36:18,217
I am deeply…

504
00:36:21,929 --> 00:36:23,723
deeply sorry.

505
00:37:56,649 --> 00:37:57,817
Sis…

506
00:38:19,088 --> 00:38:20,339
Welcome back.

507
00:38:28,806 --> 00:38:29,890
Yes.

508
00:39:04,133 --> 00:39:05,217
Ms. Kiryu.

509
00:39:07,053 --> 00:39:08,471
Thank you.

510
00:39:12,600 --> 00:39:13,726
Ever since…

511
00:39:16,854 --> 00:39:20,149
Ever since I was a child,

512
00:39:20,649 --> 00:39:24,278
if something in front of me didn't add up,
I couldn't just leave it alone.

513
00:39:25,863 --> 00:39:30,117
Revealing the truth behind things
was my way to cope

514
00:39:30,785 --> 00:39:33,996
and the only place I belonged.

515
00:39:37,666 --> 00:39:39,085
The Shiramine case

516
00:39:39,960 --> 00:39:43,381
was the only contradiction in my life

517
00:39:44,173 --> 00:39:46,467
that I turned my eyes away from.

518
00:39:47,802 --> 00:39:50,596
The reason I was obsessed
with the Shiramine incident…

519
00:39:53,349 --> 00:39:56,018
may not have been to save Mr. Serizawa.

520
00:39:57,186 --> 00:40:00,439
I think it may have been

521
00:40:01,315 --> 00:40:02,691
to save my past self.

522
00:40:08,948 --> 00:40:12,827
I want to thank you as well.

523
00:40:15,996 --> 00:40:19,083
I might have been lacking in many ways.

524
00:40:20,334 --> 00:40:21,460
All this time,

525
00:40:22,002 --> 00:40:26,173
I've always intended to face
the "loved ones" in my own way.

526
00:40:29,176 --> 00:40:32,888
I was able to see many things

527
00:40:33,472 --> 00:40:35,433
I had never seen before.

528
00:40:40,312 --> 00:40:41,856
The days I spent…

529
00:40:46,652 --> 00:40:48,446
with everyone at the MEJ…

530
00:40:50,656 --> 00:40:52,908
are something I will always treasure.

531
00:40:57,788 --> 00:40:58,831
Doctor.

532
00:41:00,124 --> 00:41:01,584
Thank you.

533
00:41:08,549 --> 00:41:09,550
Sure.

534
00:41:38,204 --> 00:41:39,580
<i>Now for the next story.</i>

535
00:41:39,663 --> 00:41:41,790
<i>In the retrial for the case</i>
<i>of a triple murder</i>

536
00:41:41,874 --> 00:41:44,502
<i>that happened in Shiramine 16 years ago,</i>

537
00:41:44,585 --> 00:41:46,962
<i>the Tokyo District Court handed down</i>

538
00:41:47,046 --> 00:41:49,798
<i>a not guilty verdict to Shinichi Serizawa,</i>

539
00:41:49,882 --> 00:41:51,884
<i>who was formerly on death row.</i>

540
00:41:55,721 --> 00:41:59,808
<i>Following this, Shinichi Serizawa</i>
<i>and his older sister, Akiko,</i>

541
00:41:59,892 --> 00:42:02,144
<i>held a press conference in Tokyo.</i>

542
00:42:03,312 --> 00:42:05,898
<i>Thanks to the support of so many people,</i>

543
00:42:05,981 --> 00:42:09,193
<i>we were able to get to this day.</i>

544
00:42:10,236 --> 00:42:12,905
<i>Thank you so very much.</i>

545
00:42:13,531 --> 00:42:14,532
Ms. Dojima!

546
00:42:14,615 --> 00:42:16,617
We found a witness!

547
00:42:17,326 --> 00:42:18,702
I'll go talk to them.

548
00:42:18,786 --> 00:42:19,787
Yes, ma'am!

549
00:42:19,870 --> 00:42:21,997
<i>We were able to keep going</i>

550
00:42:22,665 --> 00:42:24,124
<i>without giving up,</i>

551
00:42:24,208 --> 00:42:26,502
<i>because of the people</i>
<i>who stood by our side.</i>

552
00:42:27,962 --> 00:42:31,048
<i>Now, my younger brother and I</i>

553
00:42:32,132 --> 00:42:37,179
<i>would like to live in peace,</i>
<i>and treasure the time we have.</i>

554
00:42:38,180 --> 00:42:41,183
<i>There were many times, until now,</i>

555
00:42:42,518 --> 00:42:45,604
<i>when I thought it was over.</i>

556
00:42:48,816 --> 00:42:49,733
<i>But…</i>

557
00:42:52,528 --> 00:42:53,362
<i>my sister</i>

558
00:42:54,697 --> 00:42:58,450
<i>believed in me to the very end.</i>

559
00:42:58,534 --> 00:42:59,577
<i>I am so grateful.</i>

560
00:42:59,660 --> 00:43:00,953
-Kiryu!
-Yes?

561
00:43:01,036 --> 00:43:02,329
The proposal you submitted

562
00:43:02,413 --> 00:43:05,541
for the new cause-of-death
investigation system was excellent.

563
00:43:05,624 --> 00:43:06,750
Can you proceed with this?

564
00:43:07,668 --> 00:43:09,003
Thank you very much.

565
00:43:11,922 --> 00:43:12,965
That's great.

566
00:43:13,549 --> 00:43:14,675
Oh, yes.

567
00:43:20,806 --> 00:43:22,308
MAHO KIRYU

568
00:43:33,944 --> 00:43:36,905
<i>Now, with this verdict,</i>
<i>Serizawa and his family</i>

569
00:43:36,989 --> 00:43:40,492
<i>will finally be able</i>
<i>to take a new step forward.</i>

570
00:43:40,993 --> 00:43:43,412
<i>The prosecution</i>
<i>will not be submitting an appeal,</i>

571
00:43:43,495 --> 00:43:45,956
<i>and apologized to Serizawa</i>
<i>and his family, saying,</i>

572
00:43:46,040 --> 00:43:49,752
<i>"We have caused you many years of pain."</i>

573
00:44:09,813 --> 00:44:12,858
Subtitle translation by: Maslin F.
